# 🚗 Vehicle Detection and Tracking using YOLOv8 + CBAM vs Faster R-CNN

## 📌 Overview

This project presents a comprehensive evaluation of two deep learning architectures for **vehicle detection and multi-object tracking in traffic scenes**:

* **YOLOv8n with CBAM (Convolutional Block Attention Module)** — single-stage detector optimized for real-time performance.
* **Faster R-CNN (ResNet-50-FPN)** — two-stage detector focused on high localization accuracy.

The models were trained and evaluated on the **Cars Object Tracking Dataset (Unidata)** and integrated with **ByteTrack** for multi-object tracking.

Results show that **YOLOv8n+CBAM achieves higher overall detection performance and ~5× faster inference**, making it more suitable for real-time deployment.

---

## 📂 Dataset

### Cars Object Tracking Dataset — Unidata

The dataset contains **10,000+ annotated frames** extracted from real-world road traffic videos.

### Key Features

* Real-world traffic scenarios
* Temporally consistent video frames
* Polygon and bounding box annotations (`annotations.xml`)
* Designed for object detection and multi-object tracking tasks
* Continuous sequences suitable for tracking algorithms

### Vehicle Classes Used in Training

This study extends the dataset into **eight vehicle categories**:

| Class      | Description                           |
| ---------- | ------------------------------------- |
| Auto       | Three-wheeled auto-rickshaws          |
| Bus        | Passenger buses                       |
| Car        | Passenger cars and SUVs               |
| LCV        | Light commercial vehicles             |
| Motorcycle | Two-wheelers                          |
| Multiaxle  | Heavy multi-axle trucks               |
| Tractor    | Agricultural or construction vehicles |
| Truck      | Medium/heavy goods vehicles           |

